---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for Betting Maths, explaining analytics, cookies, external links, future advertising or affiliate links, and how user data may be handled."
>
  <section class="content-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy policy</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      This privacy policy explains how Betting Maths may collect, use and protect information when people use this website.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Summary:</strong> Betting Maths is an educational website. It currently uses Google Analytics to understand site usage. It may use advertising, affiliate links or additional analytics tools in the future.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths is a website available at:
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>https://www.bettingmaths.co.uk</strong>
    </p>

    <p>
      The site provides free betting calculators, guides and glossary content for educational purposes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Information we may collect</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths does not currently ask users to create accounts, log in, place bets or submit payment information.
    </p>
    <p>
      Depending on how the site is used and how it develops, information may include:
    </p>

    <ul class="standard-list">
      <li>Anonymous or aggregated website analytics data</li>
      <li>Pages visited and general usage patterns</li>
      <li>Device, browser and approximate location information provided through analytics tools</li>
      <li>Information submitted voluntarily through a future contact form or email address, if added</li>
      <li>Cookie or similar technology information used for analytics, site functionality, advertising or affiliate tracking</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Google Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths uses Google Analytics to understand how visitors use the site. This helps identify which calculators and guides are useful, which pages need improvement, and how the site is performing.
    </p>
    <p>
      Google Analytics may collect information such as page views, approximate location, device type, browser type and general interaction data.
    </p>
    <p>
      The current Google Analytics measurement ID used on the site is:
    </p>

    <div class="code-box">
      G-FFL84ZKLKK
    </div>

    <p>
      Users can manage cookies through their browser settings. Google also provides tools and information for managing how Google Analytics data is used.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
    <p>
      Cookies are small files placed on a device by websites. They can be used for site functionality, analytics, advertising, affiliate tracking and remembering preferences.
    </p>
    <p>
      Betting Maths may use cookies or similar technologies for:
    </p>

    <ul class="standard-list">
      <li>Analytics and site performance measurement</li>
      <li>Understanding which pages are most useful</li>
      <li>Future advertising or affiliate link tracking</li>
      <li>Improving the user experience</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Future improvement:</strong> If the site begins using advertising, affiliate tracking or additional non-essential cookies, a clearer cookie consent setup may be added.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Advertising and affiliate links</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths does not currently need users to pay to access calculators or guides.
    </p>
    <p>
      The site may include advertising, affiliate links or sponsored placements in the future. If affiliate links are added, Betting Maths may earn a commission when users click a link or complete an action.
    </p>
    <p>
      Any future advertising or affiliate relationships should not change the educational purpose of the site.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Contact information</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths does not currently publish a contact email address or contact form.
    </p>
    <p>
      If contact details are added in the future and users choose to send a message, the information provided may be used to respond to that message.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>External links</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths may link to third-party websites, including responsible gambling resources, official support organisations, calculators, tools, search engines, analytics providers or other informational websites.
    </p>
    <p>
      External websites have their own privacy policies and terms. Betting Maths is not responsible for the privacy practices of third-party websites.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>How information may be used</h2>
    <p>
      Information may be used to:
    </p>

    <ul class="standard-list">
      <li>Monitor site performance</li>
      <li>Understand which pages are visited</li>
      <li>Improve calculators, guides and navigation</li>
      <li>Identify technical issues</li>
      <li>Respond to messages if contact features are added</li>
      <li>Support future advertising, affiliate or monetisation features if introduced</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Data sharing</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths may use third-party services such as Google Analytics, hosting providers, domain providers or future advertising and affiliate platforms.
    </p>
    <p>
      These services may process information according to their own privacy policies and terms.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Data security</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths aims to use reputable hosting and analytics services. However, no website can guarantee complete security.
    </p>
    <p>
      Users should avoid sending sensitive personal, financial or gambling-related information unless a secure and appropriate contact method is clearly provided.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths is not intended for children. The site discusses betting maths and gambling-related terminology for educational purposes.
    </p>
    <p>
      People under the legal gambling age should not gamble.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Your choices</h2>
    <p>
      Users can:
    </p>

    <ul class="standard-list">
      <li>Use browser settings to block or delete cookies</li>
      <li>Use browser privacy tools or extensions</li>
      <li>Choose not to use the website</li>
      <li>Avoid submitting personal information if contact features are added</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Changes to this privacy policy</h2>
    <p>
      This privacy policy may be updated as Betting Maths develops, especially if new features, contact methods, advertising, affiliate links or cookie tools are added.
    </p>
    <p>
      Last updated: 3 May 2026.
    </p>

    <div class="button-row">
      <a class="button primary" href="/responsible-gambling/">Responsible Gambling</a>
      <a class="button secondary" href="/disclaimer/">Disclaimer</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .article-section {
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .standard-list {
      padding-left: 1.3rem;
    }

    .standard-list li {
      margin: 0.45rem 0;
    }

    .code-box {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 0.65rem 0.85rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
      color: var(--color-navy);
      font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", "Courier New", monospace;
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .article-section a {
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
      font-weight: 800;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }
  </style>
</MainLayout>
